This product bundles or depends on the following third-party components,
each under its own permissive license:

- pypdfium2 (Apache-2.0 / BSD-3-Clause) — wraps Google PDFium (BSD-3-Clause),
  used for PDF page rendering and text extraction.
- reportlab (BSD-3-Clause) — used to build PDF output.
- pdfplumber (MIT) — used for text-layer word bounding boxes.
- Pillow (HPND / MIT-CMU) — image drawing for redaction.
- PyThaiNLP (Apache-2.0) — Thai tokenization and NER.
- python-crfsuite (MIT) — CRF sequence labeling for the thainer NER engine.

Bundled fonts (self-hosted WOFF2 in desktop/src/fonts/ and extension/fonts/,
used for the application UI):
- IBM Plex Sans Thai Looped (SIL Open Font License 1.1) — Copyright 2017 IBM Corp.
- IBM Plex Mono (SIL Open Font License 1.1) — Copyright 2017 IBM Corp.
  Source: https://github.com/IBM/plex

Optional components (installed separately, not part of the core distribution):
- sentence-transformers / torch — optional semantic Section-26 detector.
- paddleocr / paddlepaddle / opencv — optional scanned-PDF OCR.

PyMuPDF (AGPL) is NO LONGER used; it was replaced by the permissive libraries
above so this project can be distributed under the Apache-2.0 license.
